38. Focusing on your health and learning more about your condition has made you a better mum. It’s not selfish to focus on you at times.
37. Being outside makes you feel better. Get out in nature as much as possible.

36. Love what you love. Your #Manics phase isn’t a phase. Neither is #SilentWitness These will continue into adulthood. Your husband will accept your love of Nicky Wire and Nikki Alexander but reject it as a baby name idea.
35. Your #disability doesn’t make you any less important. No matter what society says.
34. It’s okay to feel how you feel. Your feelings are valid even if someone has it worse doesn’t change how you feel.
33. Sometimes you need to end a friendship. Not because of how they treat you, but how they treat other people.
32. Don’t expect others to be as passionate about things that affect you and your life.
31. Sometimes your beliefs will change. Your perception of life and the world will change. That’s okay.

@MySpiritEvolves I have found this very therapeutic! I think years of burying feelings and charging on with life have caught up and it’s time to look at the good, what’s changed and what I’ve learned. It certainly helped empty my head and get to sleep when it was written down 💕
30. Other people will have memories of you that make them smile. Probably people you wouldn’t expect. Your existence means something to other people.
29. Find your truth. Face your truth. Speak your truth. Be your truth. Everything will catch up on you in the end. Also there is a #Manics lyric for every occasion.
28. You won’t realise at the time who the important people will be. The boy at the party who I married. The girl in the street who 16 years on is still a friend. The workmate who became family 💕
27. Sometimes you need to be the one to reach out to others. Sometimes you need to be the one to cut contact. You need to put your needs first.
26. There will be people at your wedding who five years later won’t be a part of your life. This is also okay, you were a different you then.
25. Stay weird. Stay true to you.
24. Not everyone will like you and that’s okay. It is no reflection on you as a person.
23. I like helping others and give good advice. I do not always pay attention to that advice. This list may help keep me on track.
22. Despite struggling with friendships, I can understand others needs and build strong professional relationships
21. I need lists to function
20. Planes make more sense to me than people. Planes make me happy. It doesn’t matter if no one else understands.
19. Good and bad is not black and white.
18. It takes effort to hate people. Be kind to others where you can and if you can’t be kind, walk away but do no harm.
17. Tomorrow isn’t guaranteed. We don’t know how much time we have so do what you love but don’t beat yourself up for ‘wasting’ time.
16. Writing helps me make sense of the world. Putting words on a page starts to untangle the threads in my head.

15. There is no better thing than hearing the words ‘I love you mummy’. And the answer to ‘can I have a cuddle’ is ‘always’ 💙💙
14. Tiredness and fatigue are not the same thing. Reserve your spoons. Accept you can’t do everything.
13. Trauma changes you. Accept this is not a flaw in character. But realise nothing stays buried forever.
12. ‘Secrets make you sick’. You can’t do it alone. Let others in. Talk.
11. The world isn’t fair. You need to step up and do what you can. Accept your privilege and use it to help.

10. You will be unlikely to have one definitive ‘best day ever’. The day I got married, the day I became a mum, the day number 2 son was born... there will be more to come. Don’t get hung up on the idea there will only ever be one and you have to choose which one

8. You can never have too many notebooks. Organisation is key for me.
7. I struggle to understand the intentions of others. For this reason I shut down or shut people out.
6. Not being the loudest person doesn’t make you weak.
5. Sometimes you get it wrong. Learn to listen. Learn to say sorry. And when you know you’re right have the courage to speak up.
4. We are not meant to stay the same. As we age we change. People change us, experiences change us. I am not the person I was 10 years ago  and that’s not a bad thing.
3. Sometimes I need to retreat into the world inside my head to escape the real world, but I can’t live there forever. I like it in here though.
2. Sometimes you won’t stay friends with everyone you thought you would and that’s okay. People change, lives go in different directions. And even if it hurts sometimes you have to walk away.
1. Sometimes from something bad, good will happen. Not always. But there have been times when terrible things have happened in my life, yet without them, I wouldn’t be where I am now.
